            <div id="id3" style="height: 359px; left: 350px; position: absolute; top: 66px; width: 602px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_602_359" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="Body"><br /></p>
                  <p class="Body"><br /></p>
                  <div class="paragraph Body" style="padding-bottom: 0pt; "><div id="id2" style="height: 310px; position: relative; width: 589px; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text inline-block"><div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_589_310" style="padding: 0px; "><div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default"><p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_4"><span style="line-height: 28px; " class="style_1">Consider a normal coin (heads and tails types). Probability of heads is 0.5 and tails is also 0.5. It just means that there is a 50% chance that either heads or tails will come if I toss a coin. The number 0.5 represents number of heads/total number of tosses , where number of tosses are almost infinite. If I suggest a gamble on it, that I win 1Rs/- if heads come and lose 1Rs/- if tails comes then the game is fair. Why?<br /></span></p></div></div></div></div>
